H3.text: For which group did Jimmy Page, and John Paul Jones play before they formed 'Led Zepplin'. Yardbirds

A4.text: Bassist/keyboardist/arranger John Paul Jones, who had worked with Page on countless sessions including several with the Yardbirds, approached Page and offered to be the new bassist.

A5.text: The Yardbirds are an English rock band formed in London in 1963. The band started the careers of three of rock's most famous guitarists: Eric Clapton (1963–1965), Jeff Beck (1965–1966) and Jimmy Page (1966–1968).
